Hello Longhorns! We are looking for new enthusiastic dancers to add to our team! Texas Mohini is an all-girls Bollywood fusion dance team at the University of Texas at Austin. We perform multiple dance styles including Bollywood, Bharatnatyam, Kathak, Hip-hop, Contemporary, and Bhangra. We compete all over Texas and at national competitions!!! This past year we had the honor of competing at Tamasha in San Diego, South Asian Showdown in Boston, and Tufaan in Chicago!!! 

Check out our performance from this past year!

The year may be winding down, but the fun doesn‚Äôt stop. You can put your left foot in. You can even take your left foot out. Because this is what it‚Äôs all about:

You want dancing? There‚Äôs dancing. You want singing? There‚Äôs singing. You want Ajay Patel? Good luck hearing him over the volume level of his emcee partner Sonya Joshi.        

The primary purpose of the show is to raise awareness and funds for The World Race, a program which one of our beloved alumni, Jayshree Thomas, will be participating in next year. The World Race is an 11 month mission trip that extends into 11 different countries to serve underprivileged communities. You can find out more information about her trip at: http://jayshreethomas.theworldrace.org. 

Texas Mohini is proud to support Jayshree in her noble journey to help those less fortunate. We are so excited to share our love for dance and for her mission. This event will showcase all the different styles of dance that Mohini incorporates. These styles will be featured in small and large group performances. Apart from the dancing, we have extremely talented guest singing acts that you will not want to miss! 

Doors open at 6:30 PM and the show will begin promptly at 7 PM. Tickets are $10 per person, and can be purchased here: https://www.eventbrite.com/e/texas-mohini-spring-2015-benefit-show-tickets-16671661388

(Donations are also more than welcome, and there will be an opportunity to give on the ticket page and at the show as well).      

We have had an extremely rewarding season, and could not think of a better way to end it than giving back for such a great cause! Thank you Jayshree Thomas for allowing us to be a part of your road to this amazing journey!

We hope to see you all there and HOOK EM!
